## Part 1 — Core coding (8) — Q & A

### 1. Find all permutations of a string

**Q:** Given a string (e.g. `"ABC"`), print all permutations.

**A:**

```python
from itertools import permutations

s = "ABC"
for p in permutations(s):
    print("".join(p), end="")
# Output: ABCACBBACBCACABCBA
```

